        <h2 class="text-center">Our Services</h2>
        <div class="text-center">
          <hr class="hr-center">
        </div>

        <div class="section-text">
          <p>
            Our practice is devoted to the provision of anesthesia services, including both general anesthesia and sedation, in the office of your dentist, dental specialist, or oral and maxillofacial surgeon. Office-based anesthesia services have become well established as a safe alternative to the hospital environment with proper clinician training, monitoring, preparation and experience. As such, we bring to each office all necessary anesthesia and resuscitation equipment. Each patient receives our undivided attention throughout their office visit.
            </br>
            </br>

            While receiving anesthesia services for some individuals is a natural and appropriate choice for completion of required dental / surgical treatment, parents of children and many adults may have concerns that we are happy to address. Our web site may answer some of your questions but, first and foremost, we encourage you to contact us to have all your remaining questions answered. Please feel free to ask questions throughout the treatment period, even after you are home! Nothing is more important than keeping you informed; from our initial conversations and directions on preparation for the anesthetic, to when you leave your doctor’s office comfortable and satisfied with your or your child’s recovery.

            </br>
            </br>

            As a consultant and a resource to your dentist or surgeon, we have already taken a considerable amount of time to review the anesthetic services we provide, the office resources and staff required, as well as the procedures that are followed to provide a safe anesthetic. If there is a dentist or dental specialist you wish us to contact on your behalf we will be happy to do that for you. We are frequently contacted by dentists searching for the availability of anesthesia services in the office environment.
            </br>
            </br>

            We provide office-based anesthesia services in Nassau, Suffolk, Queens, Manhattan, Rockland and Westchester County, New York, as well as in Fairfield County, Connecticut and Northern New Jersey.
          
            </br>
            </br>
          </p>
        </div>
      
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


